result.execSummary:
The defendant Jonathan Valencia was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
To be served concurrent to 17CF14 and any other current probation sentences.  Defendant has 52 days jail credit if probation is revoked.  Trempealeau County Case No. 17CM10 is dismissed and read in.

In the event that the defendant is discharged from probation with outstanding financial obligations, the supervising agent SHALL notify the court 10 days prior to the revocation or discharge.  A civil judgment SHALL be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

miscConds.notes: Restitution ordered:  A.K. - $150.00; Restitution surcharge - $15.00.  Cash bond to be applied.
Defendant to pay court costs and DNA surcharge.  Cash bond to be applied.
Defendant is to pursue and obtain HSED/GED.  Defendant is to seek and maintain full time employement and is not to terminate employment without agent's prior approval.
Defendant to complete AODA assessment and all follow through.  Defendant is to sign any releases as requested by agent.  Defendant is subject to random drug and alcohol testing.

Defendant not to possess or consume alcohol and is not to enter places where alcohol is sold for consumption on premises.  Defendant not to possess a controlled substance without a valid prescription, and is only to use prescription medications as prescribed.
Defendant is to comply and follow through with any counseling, treatment or programming as deemed appropriate by the risk/needs assessment and agent.  Defendant to submit DNA sample.
